sureSerializer` could extend the `Serializer`. I think the methods should take an Object as input and return an Object as well. This might be a key detail to implement properly, ensuring it aligns with expected behaviors. It's important to ensure consistency in how these methods operate, as that could significantly impact usability. I need to figure out if there are other aspects to consider during this setup!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_x2i7YFXHgQZX14PHn8t0PMYw|fc_0bdb2685a1b187bd0169f2795c1bac81a18ee7201985a61f25", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/src/test/java/com_esotericsoftware/kryo_shaded/ClosureSerializerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_esotericsoftware.kryo_shaded;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.Serializable;\nimport java.lang.invoke.SerializedLambda;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.Kryo;\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.Input;\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.Output;\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.serializers.ClosureSerializer;\n\npublic class ClosureSerializerTest {\n    @Test\n    void writesReadsAndCopiesSerializableClosures() {\n        Kryo kryo = newKryo();\n        ClosureSerializer serializer = new ClosureSerializer();\n        String capturedValue = \"dynamic-access\";\n        SerializableStringSupplier original = () -> \"closure-\" + capturedValue;\n\n        byte[] bytes = writeToBytes(kryo, serializer, original);\n        SerializableStringSupplier restored = readFromBytes(kryo, serializer, bytes, original.getClass());\n        SerializableStringSupplier copied = (SerializableStringSupplier) serializer.copy(kryo, original);\n\n        assertThat(restored.get()).isEqualTo(\"closure-dynamic-access\");\n        assertThat(copied.get()).isEqualTo(\"closure-dynamic-access\");\n    }\n\n    private static Kryo newKryo() {\n        Kryo kryo = new Kryo();\n        kryo.setRegistrationRequired(false);\n        kryo.setReferences(false);\n        kryo.setAsmEnabled(false);\n        kryo.register(SerializedLambda.class);\n        return kryo;\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] writeToBytes(Kryo kryo, ClosureSerializer serializer, SerializableStringSupplier value) {\n        Output output = new Output(512, -1);\n        serializer.write(kryo, output, value);\n        output.close();\n        return output.toBytes();\n    }\n\n    private static SerializableStringSupplier readFromBytes(Kryo kryo, ClosureSerializer serializer, byte[] bytes, Class<?> type) {\n        Input input = new Input(bytes);\n        SerializableStringSupplier value = (SerializableStringSupplier) serializer.read(kryo, input, type);\n        input.close();\n        return value;\n    }\n\n    @FunctionalInterface\n    private interface SerializableStringSupplier extends Serializable {\n        String get();\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.esotericsoftware/kryo-shaded/3.0.3/src/test/java/com_esotericsoftware/kryo_shaded/ClosureSerializerTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage com_esotericsoftware.kryo_shaded;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\n\\nimport java.io.Serializable;\\nimport java.lang.invoke.SerializedLambda;\\n\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.Kryo;\\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.Input;\\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.io.Output;\\nimport com.esotericsoftware.kryo.serializers.ClosureSerializer;\\n\\npublic class ClosureSerializerTest {\\n    @Test\\n    void writesReadsAndCopiesSerializableClosures() {\\n        Kryo kryo = newKryo();\\n        ClosureSerializer serializer = new ClosureSerializer();\\n        String capturedValue = \\\"dynamic-access\\\";\\n        SerializableStringSupplier original = () -> \\\"closure-\\\" + capturedValue;\\n\\n        byte[] bytes = writeToBytes(kryo, serializer, original);\\n        SerializableStringSupplier restored = readFromBytes(kryo, serializer, bytes, original.getClass());\\n        SerializableStringSupplier copied = (SerializableStringSupplier) serializer.copy(kryo, original);\\n\\n        assertThat(restored.get()).isEqualTo(\\\"closure-dynamic-access\\\");\\n        assertThat(copied.get()).isEqualTo(\\\"closure-dynamic-access\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Kryo newKryo() {\\n        Kryo kryo = new Kryo();\\n        kryo.setRegistrationRequired(false);\\n        kryo.setReferences(false);\\n        kryo.setAsmEnabled(false);\\n        kryo.register(SerializedLambda.class);\\n        return kryo;\\n    }\\n\\n    private static byte[] writeToBytes(Kryo kryo, ClosureSerializer serializer, SerializableStringSupplier value) {\\n        Output output = new Output(512, -1);\\n        serializer.write(kryo, output, value);\\n        output.close();\\n        return output.toBytes();\\n    }\\n\\n    private static SerializableStringSupplier readFromBytes(Kryo kryo, ClosureSerializer serializer, byte[] bytes, Class<?> type) {\\n        Input input = new Input(bytes);\\n        SerializableStringSupplier value = (SerializableStringSupplier) serializer.read(kryo, input, type);\\n        input.close();\\n        return value;\\n    }\\n\\n    @FunctionalInterface\\n    private interface SerializableStringSupplier extends Serializable {\\n        String get();\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1469, "output": 1528, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33717, "cost": {"input": 0, "ou